## 6. Functional requirements

### FR-1 Budget groups

- FR-1.1 Create unlimited groups: name, icon (from icon picker), color (from palette).
- FR-1.2 “Personal” group seeded on first launch.
- FR-1.3 Add members to a group: pick from existing people or create a new person (name + color).
- FR-1.4 Optional budget limits: any combination of daily/monthly/yearly.
- FR-1.5 `carry_over` toggle: unspent budget from a period rolls into the next.
- FR-1.6 Archive a group (hidden in main list, accessible via filter, all data retained).
- FR-1.7 Delete a group (soft delete: `is_deleted = 1`; data retained for balance history).

### FR-2 Transactions

- FR-2.1 Two user-created kinds: `income` and `expense`. (`settlement` is system-created only — never shown in the add flow.)
- FR-2.2 Required fields: amount, date (default today), category, at least one payer, shares. Optional: note, photo, tags.
- FR-2.3 Custom categories per group. Default list seeded (§3). User can add/rename/delete.
- FR-2.4 Recurring transactions: set frequency (daily/weekly/monthly/custom interval). Future instances materialize lazily when the relevant date range is viewed — not generated upfront. Editing a recurring txn prompts: “This instance only” or “This and all future.”
- FR-2.5 Tags: free-text, prefixed with `#`. Used for cross-group filtering in Reports.
- FR-2.6 Edit any transaction. Soft-delete (is_deleted = 1). Balances recompute automatically.

### FR-3 Split engine

- FR-3.1 **Split types:**
  
  |Type          |Behavior                                                          |
  |--------------|------------------------------------------------------------------|
  |Equal         |Total shared equally among selected members                       |
  |Exact         |User enters exact paise amount per person                         |
  |Percentage    |User enters % per person; must total 100%                         |
  |Shares (ratio)|User enters ratio units (e.g. 2:1:1); auto-computes amounts       |
  |Itemized      |Driven by line items (FR-4); shares computed from item assignments|
- FR-3.2 Multiple payers per transaction: split the “who paid” side among any members.
- FR-3.3 Exclude any member from a specific split without removing them from the group.
- FR-3.4 **Invariant enforcement:** Save button is disabled until `Σ txn_payment == Σ txn_share`. A signed live remainder is shown (e.g. “₹50 unassigned” or “₹50 over-assigned”).
- FR-3.5 Shares stored explicitly in `txn_share` at save time. Never recomputed later from the split type — the frozen amounts are the source of truth.
- FR-3.6 **Paise rounding rule:** When dividing an amount that doesn’t divide evenly, the remainder paise go to the earliest-listed members one paise each. Final totals must sum to exactly the original amount. No paise created or lost.

### FR-4 Itemized bill entry

- FR-4.1 Add line items: name, qty (integer), unit price (paise). Running subtotal shown live.
- FR-4.2 Add tax, tip, or discount: either a flat paise amount or a percentage of the subtotal. Applied proportionally across all items (affects per-item price for assignment math).
- FR-4.3 Each line item is assigned to one or more members. A line item’s cost is split equally among its assignees (paise rounding per FR-3.6).
- FR-4.4 Per-person running total updates live on every assignment change.
- FR-4.5 **Quick-assign UX:** Tap a line item row → member avatar row appears below it. Tap avatar to assign/unassign. With many members, avatar row scrolls horizontally. Most recently used members float to the left.
- FR-4.6 “Split the rest equally” button: assigns all currently-unassigned items equally across all group members.
- FR-4.7 On confirm: line item assignments are collapsed into per-person `txn_share` amounts. Payers set on a separate step (same flow, next screen). Invariant check before final save.
- FR-4.8 Attach a photo of the receipt (no OCR — manual entry only in v1).

### FR-5 Debt simplification

- FR-5.1 Compute net balance per member in scope (per-group or global across all groups).
- FR-5.2 Apply greedy min-cash-flow algorithm (§8) to reduce to fewest settlements.
- FR-5.3 **Settle-Up screen** shows a simple list: “Rahul pays GF ₹450”.
- FR-5.4 “Mark as Paid” on a settlement creates a `settlement` txn (auditable history). Balances update immediately.
- FR-5.5 **Global Settle-Up:** nets balances across ALL groups into the minimum cross-person payments. Entry point from the dashboard.

### FR-6 Global dashboard

- FR-6.1 Three tabs: **Today / This Month / This Year**
- FR-6.2 “My Spending” = Σ my `txn_share` amounts in the selected period (not what I paid).
- FR-6.3 Metrics shown: my income, my spending, net (income − spending), savings rate %.
- FR-6.4 Category donut chart (my spending by category) + bar chart (spending over time — daily/weekly/monthly depending on tab).
- FR-6.5 “You owe / you’re owed” total across all groups with a “Settle Up” button → global settle-up screen.
- FR-6.6 Per-group budget health chips: group name + progress bar + color (green <80%, amber 80–100%, red >100%).

### FR-7 Budget tracking and alerts

- FR-7.1 Per-group limits (any combination of daily/monthly/yearly). Plus a separate **global personal limit** configurable in Settings — independent of any group, tracking only my shares.
- FR-7.2 **Local notifications** when any limit hits 80% and 100%. Uses `expo-notifications`. Scheduled locally — no server.
- FR-7.3 Budget progress bar on group card (groups list) and at the top of group detail.
- FR-7.4 Carry-over: if enabled for a group, remaining budget from the prior period is added to the current period’s limit for comparison.

### FR-8 Reports and export

- FR-8.1 Per-group monthly summary: total income, total expense, net savings, top 3 categories by spend.
- FR-8.2 Export transaction list as **CSV** (all fields) and **PDF** (formatted summary) via native share sheet (`expo-sharing`). Scoped to the current date filter.
- FR-8.3 Date range filter (custom from/to dates) available in Reports.
- FR-8.4 Year-in-review screen: total saved this year, biggest spending month, most-used category, biggest single expense.

### FR-9 Sync `[v2 only — skip in v1]`

- FR-9.1 Supabase email or Apple sign-in. Only required when sharing a group.
- FR-9.2 Personal groups (is_shared = 0) never leave the device.
- FR-9.3 Marking a group shared uploads group + all its txns to Supabase. Members linked by `remote_uid`.
- FR-9.4 Invite by 6-character join code mapping to group id.
- FR-9.5 Supabase Realtime channel per shared group; inbound changes merged into SQLite.
- FR-9.6 Conflict rule: last-write-wins by `updated_at`. Soft-deletes always win over edits.
- FR-9.7 Offline edits enqueue locally; flush on reconnect.

