## 11. Edge cases (must handle — these are where bugs live)

|Case                                              |Required behavior                                                                                                                                                       |
|--------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|`Σ paid ≠ Σ share` at save                        |Save button disabled. Show signed remainder in red. Highlight the unbalanced side.                                                                                      |
|Percentage split ≠ 100%                           |Save blocked. Show delta (e.g. “3% unassigned”).                                                                                                                        |
|Zero-amount split member                          |Allowed (e.g. a member excluded but still in the group). Store 0 in txn_share.                                                                                          |
|Paise rounding on equal split                     |Use `splitEqual()` helper. Largest-index members get the floor, earliest get the ceiling. Sum must be exact.                                                            |
|Member removed from group with open balance       |Block removal. Show: “Settle up with [name] first.” Allow force-remove only after showing the outstanding amount.                                                       |
|Deleting a txn that was already settled           |Allowed. Soft-delete it. Recompute balances. The settlement txn remains; net may become non-zero again (user must re-settle).                                           |
|Editing the amount of a split txn                 |Re-open split screen with old split type pre-filled. User must rebalance and re-save.                                                                                   |
|Recurring txn in a date range query               |Materialize instances lazily: compute all dates between query start and end using recur_freq + recur_interval + recur_end, yield virtual txn rows. Do not persist these.|
|Income in a shared group                          |Counts to group income total. Counts to the payer’s personal income. Not split — no shares for income txns (txn_share empty for income).                                |
|Global budget vs group budget                     |Completely independent. Both can fire notifications. Neither overrides the other.                                                                                       |
|Self-only transaction (no split)                  |txn_payment = [{me, amount}], txn_share = [{me, amount}]. Invariant trivially holds.                                                                                    |
|Multiple payers exact amounts don’t cover total   |Same invariant: Σ paid must equal Σ share = bill total. Enforce on payer side too.                                                                                      |
|Large group itemized bill (10+ members, 20+ items)|Line item list and avatar row must both be virtualized (FlatList). No jank.                                                                                             |
|First launch                                      |Seed DB. Show empty Personal group. Prompt to add first transaction.                                                                                                    |
|Budget carry-over calculation                     |`remaining = limit + unused_prior_period`. Only compute if carry_over = 1. Cap carry-over at one period back (don’t accumulate indefinitely).                           |

