### 16.7 Motion and interaction

- **Transitions:** React Navigation default slide (iOS feel). No custom page transitions — they add jank and look AI-generated.
- **Save feedback:** On successful save, the FAB briefly pulses (scale 1 → 1.1 → 1, 200ms, `Animated.spring`). Transaction row slides in at the top of the list.
- **Swipe to delete:** `react-native-gesture-handler` swipe left on TransactionRow → reveals red delete zone. Single swipe = soft delete.
- **Balance number update:** When a settlement is marked paid, the amount animates to ₹0.00 (cross-fade, 300ms). Not a bounce — a ledger closing.
- **Everything else:** no animation. Deliberately still. Motion is used only where it communicates a state change.

-----

### 16.8 Empty states

Every empty list has two elements only: a short factual label and one action button. No illustrations, no emoji, no motivational copy.

|Screen             |Empty label                    |Action              |
|-------------------|-------------------------------|--------------------|
|Dashboard (no txns)|“No transactions yet”          |“Add expense”       |
|Group transactions |“Nothing logged in [Group]”    |“Add expense”       |
|Settle Up          |“All settled up”               |— (no action needed)|
|Reports            |“No transactions in this range”|“Change dates”      |

-----

### 16.9 Error and validation states

- Unbalanced split: red signed remainder below the split row. “₹50 over-assigned” or “₹50 unassigned”. Save button stays grey/disabled.
- Empty required field: field border turns `expense` red on blur. No modal alerts for validation — inline only.
- Delete confirmation: bottom sheet (not alert dialog). “Delete this transaction?” with two buttons: “Delete” (red text) and “Cancel”. No destructive action via an alert.
- Failed save (DB error): toast at bottom, `bgCard` background, `expense` left border. “Couldn’t save. Try again.” Auto-dismisses in 3s.

-----

### 16.10 Tab bar

Four tabs. No labels — icons only (with accessibility labels set). Active icon fills with `accent` color; inactive = `textMuted`.

|Tab      |Icon         |Screen         |
|---------|-------------|---------------|
|Dashboard|`home`       |Global overview|
|Groups   |`layers`     |Group list     |
|Reports  |`bar-chart-2`|Reports        |
|Settings |`settings`   |Settings       |

FAB sits centered above the tab bar, not inside it. It is not a fifth tab.
